The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The local variable 'pos' is declared as 'struct MHD_HTTP_Req_Header *pos' but is only used for read-only access (iterated and its members are inspected). Per MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13, the pointer should point to a const-qualified type when possible. Declaring it as 'const struct MHD_HTTP_Req_Header *pos' would satisfy the rule. Note: other pointers in the fragment (key, pos->header, pos->value, value_ptr) are already const-qualified, so the only violation in this fragment is the non-const 'pos' pointer.
